One of the most common algebraic operations in game development is Linear Interpolation (Lerp), used to smoothly blend between two values over time:

```cpp
// Algebraic Formula: Result = A + t * (B - A)
float Lerp(float A, float B, float t) {
    // Clamp t between 0.0 and 1.0
    if (t < 0.0f) t = 0.0f;
    if (t > 1.0f) t = 1.0f;
    return A + t * (B - A);
}
```
